<p><b>Frank Miller</b> (born January 27, 1957) is an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Writer" title="Writer">writer</a>, <a href="/wiki/Artist" title="Artist">artist</a> and <a href="/wiki/Film_director" title="Film director">film director</a> best known for his dark, <a href="/wiki/Film_noir" title="Film noir">film noir</a>-style <a href="/wiki/Comic_book" title="Comic book">comic book</a> stories and <a href="/wiki/Graphic_novels" title="Graphic novels" class="mw-redirect">graphic novels</a> for <a href="/wiki/Dark_Horse_Comics" title="Dark Horse Comics">Dark Horse Comics</a>, <a href="/wiki/DC_Comics" title="DC Comics">DC Comics</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Marvel_Comics" title="Marvel Comics">Marvel Comics</a>.</p>
